reviewText: I thought there would be more than what I got, I guess I need to look harder next time as to what is included. I'd still recommend it to a friend if they like Frank Sinatra.

reviewText: This is a very good mini series.  It gives the viewer an insight to the struggle and stamina that Frank Sinatra had to get where he wanted to be.  It also you an idea as to what kind of a person he was.
summary: Sinatra:  THey Were The Very Good Years

reviewText: Really disappointed.  The edits between some of the video cuts were rough and left me wondering where it was produced.  I couldn't stand the voice of the narrator.  Sounded like someone who just graduated from broadcasting school and impressed with the sound of his own voice.  Take a pass.  I'm sure there are better docs out there on Frank!
